<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id621c9936-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s175"><num value="175">§ 175.</num><heading> United States attorneys to represent Indians</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In all States and Territories where there are reservations or allotted Indians the United States attorney shall represent them in all suits at law and in equity.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id621c9937-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1893-03-03/ch209/s1">Mar. 3, 1893, ch. 209, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/27/631">27 Stat. 631</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646/s1">June 25, 1948, ch. 646, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/909">62 Stat. 909</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id621c9938-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id621c9939-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I78" topic="changeOfName" id="id621c993a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Change of Name</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">“United States attorney” substituted in text for “United States district attorney” on authority of act <date date="1948-06-25">June 25, 1948</date>. See <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s541">section 541 of Title 28</ref>, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure.</p>
</note>
</notes>
